Connect to your server
Connecting to your Aternos Minecraft server is a simple process: just start your server and enter the server address in your Minecraft client. However, you may occasionally run into connection issues. In this article, we'll explain how to connect and provide solutions for any problems you might encounter while connecting.

How to connect to your server:
To connect to your server, copy the server address and enter it in your Minecraft client, as a new server or with "Direct Connect". You can find the server address on the server page.

This address includes your server port if "Cracked" is enabled in the options. Read more details about cracked launchers, especially TLauncher, here.

Connection issues? Here's how to fix them:
Sometimes, connecting may fail on the first attempt due to various reasons. Most of time you will get a error message like:

Internal Exception java.net.SocketException: Connection reset 
